     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>VVHo so is bound for another mane debt,</l>
      <l>doth bring himselfe in care:</l>
      <l>And is compeld to pay the same,</l>
      <l>though he be poore and bare.</l>
      <l>In euery degree loue honesty,</l>
      <l>be shamefac'd to doe euill:</l>
      <l>Ill company see that thou fly,</l>
      <l>as members of the Deuill.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>A word once spoke it can returne no more,</l>
      <l>But flies away, and oft thy bane doth breed,</l>
      <l>A wiseman sets a hatch before the doore,</l>
      <l>And whilst he may doth frame his words with heed.</l>
      <l>The bird in hand we may at will restraine,</l>
      <l>But being flown we call her back in vaine.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
